# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The problem is asking us to find all the videos that are watched by the friends of a given person (id) within a certain level of friendship. To solve this problem, we can use a breadth-first search algorithm to find all the friends within the specified level and then keep track of the videos that are watched by these friends using a frequency map.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Create a frequency map to keep track of the number of times each video is watched by the friends.
- Use a breadth-first search algorithm to find all the friends within the specified level.
- For each friend found in step 2, add their watched videos to the frequency map.
- Sort the frequency map by the number of times each video is watched.
- Return the videos in the frequency map in sorted order.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

